Senate Committee on Indian Affairs

Help

About Senate Committee on Indian Affairs

About Senate Committee on Indian Affairs

The Senate Committee on Indian Affairs was initially established as the Select Committee on Indian Affairs. Section 25 of S. Res. 71, 103rd Congress, 1st Session, redesignated it as the Committee on Indian Affairs. The jurisdiction of the Committee on Indian Affairs is specified in Senate Document 106-6.

Visit the committee's website for more information including membership and rules.

See the latest committee rules as printed in the Congressional Record.

The publications on this page are available at the committee's discretion. A "No results found" message below means there are currently no applicable publications in the system.
